tables.table_schema: CREATE TABLE customer_behavior (  customer_id INT PRIMARY KEY,  customer_name VARCHAR(50),  transaction_date DATE,  transaction_amount DECIMAL(10, 2),  product_category VARCHAR(50),  product_name VARCHAR(50) )

CREATE TABLE customers (
    customer_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_name VARCHAR(50),
    email_address VARCHAR(100),
    phone_number VARCHAR(15)
)

CREATE TABLE transactions (
    transaction_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id UUID REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    transaction_date TIMESTAMP,
    amount DECIMAL(10,2),
    product_id UUID
)

CREATE TABLE products (
    product_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    product_name VARCHAR(50),
    category VARCHAR(30),
    price DECIMAL(10,2)
)

CREATE TABLE purchases (
    purchase_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    customer_id UUID REFERENCES customers(customer_id),
    product_id UUID REFERENCES products(product_id),
    quantity INT,
    purchase_date TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE transactions(
  transaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  customer_id INT,
  date TIMESTAMP,
  amount DECIMAL(10, 2),
  product_id INT
)
